						Gradient Boosting
Gradient Boosting is a powerful ensemble learning algorithm that builds multiple Decision Trees sequentially, where each new tree learns from the errors of the previous one. This approach significantly improves prediction accuracy for both classification and regression tasks. The four major types are AdaBoost, XGBoost, LightGBM, and CatBoost, each designed for different scenarios. Gradient Boosting is widely used in finance, healthcare, recommendation systems, fraud detection, and predictive analytics because of its high accuracy and strong performance on structured data.
						
Applications
• Medical Diagnosis 
• Fraud Detection 
• Customer Churn Prediction 
• Credit Risk Analysis 
• Recommendation Systems 
• Sales Forecasting 
• Search Ranking 
• Stock Market Prediction

