2.1 AdaBoost (Adaptive Boosting)
Definition
AdaBoost is the first and one of the simplest boosting algorithms. It builds multiple weak learners (usually decision stumps), where each new learner focuses more on the samples that were incorrectly classified by previous learners. Misclassified samples receive higher weights, forcing the next learner to improve those predictions. The final prediction is obtained by combining the weighted predictions of all learners.
