2.2 XGBoost (Extreme Gradient Boosting)
Definition
XGBoost (Extreme Gradient Boosting) is an advanced implementation of Gradient Boosting designed for high speed, efficiency, and accuracy. It uses regularization techniques to reduce overfitting and supports parallel processing for faster training. XGBoost is widely used in machine learning competitions and real-world predictive analytics due to its excellent performance.
