                         │
                         ▼
             Repeat Until Convergence
                         │
                         ▼
                 Final Prediction
Examples
	• Credit Risk Prediction 
	• Loan Approval 
	• Sales Forecasting 
	• Disease Prediction 

2.3 LightGBM (Light Gradient Boosting Machine)
Definition
LightGBM is a fast and memory-efficient Gradient Boosting algorithm developed by Microsoft. It grows trees leaf-wise instead of level-wise, which usually leads to better accuracy and faster training. LightGBM is especially suitable for large datasets and applications requiring high performance.
