                         │
                         ▼
              Correct Previous Errors
                         │
                         ▼
                 Final Prediction
Examples
	• Customer Churn Prediction 
	• Product Recommendation 
	• Credit Card Fraud Detection 
	• Marketing Analysis 

3. Working of Gradient Boosting
Step 1: Collect the Dataset
Prepare the labeled training data.
Example
Age	Income	Loan
25	30000	Rejected
35	60000	Approved
40	70000	Approved

Step 2: Train the First Decision Tree
The first tree makes initial predictions.

Step 3: Calculate Errors
The algorithm computes the difference between the actual values and predicted values.
This difference is called the Residual (Error).

Step 4: Train the Next Tree
The second tree is trained specifically to correct the mistakes made by the first tree.

Step 5: Repeat the Process
Additional trees continue to reduce the remaining errors until satisfactory performance is achieved.

Step 6: Combine All Trees
The predictions from all trees are combined to generate the final output.

Example
Suppose a bank wants to predict whether a customer will repay a loan.
First Tree
